{"doc":{"isMarkdown":true,"isTranslated":false,"isActive":true,"flaws":{},"title":"Presentation.receiver","mdn_url":"/en-US/docs/Web/API/Presentation/receiver","locale":"en-US","native":"English (US)","sidebarHTML":"<ol><li><strong><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/Presentation\"><code>Presentation</code></a></strong></li><li class=\"toggle\"><details open=\"\"><summary>Properties</summary><ol><li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/Presentation/defaultRequest\"><code>defaultRequest</code></a></li><li><em><code>receiver</code></em></li></ol></details></li></ol>","body":[{"type":"prose","value":{"id":null,"title":null,"isH3":false,"content":"<p>\n  The <strong>read-only</strong> <a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/Presentation\"><code>Presentation</code></a> attribute\n  <code>receiver</code>, which is only available in browser contexts which are\n  <strong>receiving</strong> a presentation, returns the\n  <a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/PresentationReceiver\"><code>PresentationReceiver</code></a> object which can be used to access and communicate\n  with the browser context which controls the presentation. This property is always\n  <code>null</code> when accessed from outside a browser context which is receiving a\n  presentation.\n</p>"}},{"type":"prose","value":{"id":"value","title":"Value","isH3":false,"content":"<p>\n  If the code is running in a context which is receiving a presentation, the returned\n  value is a <a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/PresentationReceiver\"><code>PresentationReceiver</code></a> which can then be used to communicate\n  with the context which is the source of the presentation.\n</p>\n<p>\n  If the current context is not receiving a presentation, <code>receiver</code> is\n  <code>null</code>.\n</p>"}},{"type":"prose","value":{"id":"examples","title":"Examples","isH3":false,"content":""}},{"type":"prose","value":{"id":"determining_whether_or_not_the_context_is_receiving_a_presentation","title":"Determining whether or not the context is receiving a presentation","isH3":true,"content":"<p>\n  You can easily determine whether or not the context is the receiver for a presentation\n  by checking the value of <code>navigator.receiver</code>. If it's a non-null value, then\n  the context is indeed receiving a presentation. If it's <code>null</code>, there's no\n  incoming presentation.\n</p>\n<div class=\"code-example\"><pre class=\"brush: js notranslate\"><code><span class=\"token keyword\">if</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span>navigator<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span>receiver<span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>\n  footer<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span>innerHTML <span class=\"token operator\">=</span> <span class=\"token string\">\"Receiving presentation\"</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n<span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span>  <span class=\"token keyword\">else</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>\n  footer<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span>innerHTML <span class=\"token operator\">=</span> <span class=\"token string\">\"(idle)\"</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n<span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span>\n</code></pre></div>"}},{"type":"prose","value":{"id":"accessing_the_connection_list","title":"Accessing the connection list","isH3":true,"content":"<p>\n  This example uses <code>receiver</code> to access the list of incoming connections and\n  to build and display a list of those connections' ID strings.\n</p>\n<div class=\"code-example\"><pre class=\"brush: js notranslate\"><code><span class=\"token keyword\">let</span> listElem <span class=\"token operator\">=</span> document<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span><span class=\"token function\">getElementById</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token string\">\"connectionview\"</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n\nnavigator<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span>presentation<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span>receiver<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span>connectionList\n          <span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span><span class=\"token function\">then</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token keyword\">function</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token parameter\">connections</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>\n    connections<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span><span class=\"token function\">forEach</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token keyword\">function</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token parameter\">aConnection</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>\n      listElem<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span>innerHTML <span class=\"token operator\">+=</span> <span class=\"token string\">\"&lt;li&gt;\"</span> <span class=\"token operator\">+</span> aConnection<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span>id\n            <span class=\"token operator\">+</span> <span class=\"token string\">\"&lt;/li&gt;\"</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n    <span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n<span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n</code></pre></div>\n<p>\n  After getting access to the output list element in the variable\n  <code>connectionView</code>, <a class=\"page-not-created\" title=\"The documentation about this has not yet been written; please consider contributing!\"><code>navigator.receiver</code></a> is used to get a\n  reference to the <a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/PresentationReceiver\"><code>PresentationReceiver</code></a> object for this context, and its\n  <a class=\"page-not-created\" title=\"The documentation about this has not yet been written; please consider contributing!\"><code>connectionList</code></a> is used to get a\n  <a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/Promise\"><code>Promise</code></a> which will be called when the list is available.\n</p>\n<p>\n  The promise handler receives as its input parameter an array of the incoming\n  connections. We iterate over these using <a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/Array/forEach\"><code>forEach()</code></a>,\n  appending a new item to the <code>connectionView</code> list element for each\n  connection.\n</p>"}},{"type":"specifications","value":{"title":"Specifications","id":"specifications","isH3":false,"specifications":[{"bcdSpecificationURL":"https://w3c.github.io/presentation-api/#dom-presentation-receiver","title":"Presentation API"}],"query":"api.Presentation.receiver"}},{"type":"browser_compatibility","value":{"title":"Browser compatibility","id":"browser_compatibility","isH3":false,"query":"api.Presentation.receiver","dataURL":"/en-US/docs/Web/API/Presentation/receiver/bcd.json"}},{"type":"prose","value":{"id":"see_also","title":"See also","isH3":false,"content":"<ul>\n  <li>Presentation API</li>\n  <li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/Presentation\"><code>Presentation</code></a></li>\n  <li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/PresentationReceiver\"><code>PresentationReceiver</code></a></li>\n</ul>"}}],"toc":[{"text":"Value","id":"value"},{"text":"Examples","id":"examples"},{"text":"Specifications","id":"specifications"},{"text":"Browser compatibility","id":"browser_compatibility"},{"text":"See also","id":"see_also"}],"summary":"The read-only Presentation attribute\n  receiver, which is only available in browser contexts which are\n  receiving a presentation, returns the\n  PresentationReceiver object which can be used to access and communicate\n  with the browser context which controls the presentation. This property is always\n  null when accessed from outside a browser context which is receiving a\n  presentation.","popularity":0,"modified":"2022-03-31T05:23:18.000Z","source":{"folder":"en-us/web/api/presentation/receiver","github_url":"https://github.com/mdn/content/blob/style/old/files/en-us/web/api/presentation/receiver/index.md","last_commit_url":"https://github.com/mdn/content/commit/dc13bbc18ba23a2d86e15ff8deff8e6825ae9934","filename":"index.md"},"parents":[{"uri":"/en-US/docs/Web","title":"Web technology for developers"},{"uri":"/en-US/docs/Web/API","title":"Web APIs"},{"uri":"/en-US/docs/Web/API/Presentation","title":"Presentation"},{"uri":"/en-US/docs/Web/API/Presentation/receiver","title":"Presentation.receiver"}],"pageTitle":"Presentation.receiver - Web APIs | MDN","noIndexing":false}}